Leicester City striker, Jamie Vardy, continues to lead the scoring chart after Match Day 14 in the Premier League. Vardy scored the equalizer, as the Foxes came from behind to beat Everton 2-1 at the King Power Stadium on Sunday. It took his tally to 13 goals. Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang scored twice, as Arsenal drew 2-2 at Norwich City. Aubameyang has now struck 10 times in the league. Premier League top scorers: 13 goals: Jamie Vardy (Leicester City) 10 goals: Tammy Abraham (Chelsea), Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal) 9 goals: Sergio Aguero (Manchester City) 8 goals: Sadio Mane (Liverpool), Harry Kane (Tottenham), Raheem Sterling (Manchester City) 7 goals: Teemu Pukki (Norwich), Danny Ings (Southampton), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United). 6 goals: Mohamed Salah (Liverpool), Raul Jimenez (Wolves), Chris Wood (Burnley), Ashley Barnes (Burnley). 5 goals: Callum Wilson (Bournemouth), Christian Pulisic (Chelsea), Bernardo Silva (Manchester City). 4 goals: James Maddison (Leicester). Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.